from torchdata.datapipes.iter import IterableWrapper

def flatted_func(x):
    return [x, x+"_1", x+"_2"]

source_dp = IterableWrapper(["a", "b", "c"])
# I want to augment the source datapipe with the above function, which will return nine elements.
# Then we flatten the nine elements into a single datapipe.
new_dp = source_dp.flatmap(flatted_func).concat()
